d 'XTPUNITCOINT': module to compute panel cointegration and stationarity tests with structural breaks and common factors
d
d   The xtpunitcoint package provides three commands for panel data
d analysis: (1) xtpcointegwe implements the panel cointegration
d test of Westerlund and Edgerton (2008, Oxford Bulletin of
d Economics and Statistics). Tests the null hypothesis of no
d cointegration allowing for structural breaks (level shift or
d regime shift) and cross-sectional dependence via common factors
d estimated by principal components with Bai-Ng (2002) factor
d selection. (2) xtpcointegboot implements the bootstrap panel
d cointegration test of Westerlund and Edgerton (2007, Economics
d Letters). Tests the null hypothesis of cointegration using the
d McCoskey-Kao (1998) LM+ statistic with sieve bootstrap critical
d values to correct for size distortions under cross-sectional
d dependence. (3) )xtpkpss implements the panel KPSS stationarity
d test of Carrion-i-Silvestre, del Barrio-Castro, and López-Bazo
d (2005, Econometrics Journal). Tests the null of stationarity
d allowing for multiple structural breaks at unknown dates,
d detected via sequential Bai-Perron (1998) testing with the LWZ
d information criterion. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: cointegration
d KW: structural breaks
d KW: common factors
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260327
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtpcointegboot.ado
f xtpcointegboot.sthlp
f xtpcointegwe.ado
f xtpcointegwe.sthlp
f xtpkpss.ado
f xtpkpss.sthlp
f ../_/_xtpcointegboot_engine.ado
f ../_/_xtpcointegwe_engine.ado
f ../_/_xtpkpss_engine.ado
f xtpunitcoint_example.do
